-- Shanghai Lengguang Rises After Saying Turbine Blade Plant Planned in China
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-27T06:37:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/shanghai-lengguang-rises-after-saying-turbine-blade-plant-planned-in-china.html
Shanghai Lengguang Industrial Co.
shares rose in Shanghai after saying its plans to build a plant
to make wind-turbine blades in China’s eastern Jiangsu province.  The Shanghai-based company soared as much as 8.5 percent to
14.62 yuan, the biggest intraday increase since Sept. 15. It
rose 2.5 percent to 13.8 yuan as of 2:30 p.m. local time, while
the benchmark Shanghai Composite Index fell 1.29 percent.  The company’s unit, Shanghai FRP Research Institute Co.,
plans to invest 150 million yuan ($22.6 million) to build the
plant to make blades for 630 megawatts of wind turbines annually
in Dongtai, Jiangsu, Shanghai Lengguang said in a filing to
Shanghai’s stock exchange Dec. 25.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 swong139@bloomberg.net  